frameDefinitions: A Person has a particular mental state and the ability to engage in an activity with enthusiasm, energy, and positivity.
This frame contains words which name permanent fixed structures forming an enclosure and providing protection from the elements.
A Protagonist is in the dynamic, maintained state of being alive or has exited this state.
This frame has to do with the bias or lack of bias of a Judge making an assessment concerning two or more Sides.
Lexical units in this frame refer to Electricity, in particular as a form of energy harnessed for particular uses (such as powering machines).
The LUs in this frame refer to biological entities labeled by the FE Organism.
frameExamples: The baroque <t>church</t>, built in 1635, has a very rich interior
A compound to generate wind <t>electricity</t> was built on the other side of those mountains.
NASA may someday discover a new <t>lifeform</t> from another planet.
listRoleDefinitions: The person who is evaluated for a level of enthusiasm.
The entity built by the <fen>Builder</fen> which has some <fen>Function</fen>.
<fen>Protagonist</fen> identifies the being or entity that is  dead or alive.
This role identifies the <fen>Figure</fen> or form being described by the target.
The time in which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> is dead or alive.
This Frame Element marks the person whose objectivity in making assesment is being evaluated.
This Frame Element marks one of the <fen>Sides</fen> in a dispute or one of the alternatives in a situation of choice.
This Frame Element marks phrases jointly expressing both <fen>Sides</fen> in a dispute or all of the alternatives in a situation of choice.
The second-mentioned of the <fen>Sides</fen> to a dispute or alternatives in a situation of choice.
This Frame Element marks expressions that indicate how the bias of the <fen>Judge</fen> expresses itself in their behavior or actions.
The <fen>Dispute</fen> is the situation in which there is some conflict between two sides.
The <fen>Expressor</fen> is the body part or action by a body part which indicates the character of the <fen>Decision_maker</fen>.
This role denotes the time when the partiality occurs.
<fen>Electricity</fen> is the physical force that is used as power.
An organic that has naturally occuring bioligical processes and functions.
listRoleExamples: <fex>The referee</fex> was totally biased against our team.
The umpire was partial <fex>to the home team</fex>.
The judge was neutral <fex>between the parties</fex>.
The judge favored the defendant <fex>over the plaintiff</fex>.
My sister remained neutral <fex>in our disputes</fex>.
He had a neutral <fex>smile</fex> on his face.
The Brunswick Electric Membership Corporation supplies <fex><t>electricity</t></fex> for sections of Brunswick and Columbus counties.
